 {"id":"asupersync-1qfd0.513","title":"[audit][service-buffer] Wake inner readiness waiters after active completion","description":"Fresh-eyes audit child under asupersync-1qfd0. In src/service/buffer.rs, BufferFuture::Active wakes ready_wakers when a request completes but does not wake sibling inner_wakers, even though drop paths do. That can strand buffered requests waiting on inner readiness after the active request frees the service. Fix the completion path to wake inner readiness waiters, add a focused regression with a single-flight service that only becomes ready after the first response completes, and validate with rch-backed targeted tests/check/clippy plus fmt check.","status":"closed","priority":2,"issue_type":"bug","assignee":"BeigeCardinal","created_at":"2026-04-01T19:16:49.080966790Z","created_by":"ubuntu","updated_at":"2026-04-01T19:35:13.596771301Z","closed_at":"2026-04-01T19:35:13.596287953Z","close_reason":"Fixed and validated with rch-backed test/check/clippy","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0,"labels":["audit","buffer","liveness","service"],"dependencies":[{"issue_id":"asupersync-1qfd0.513","depends_on_id":"asupersync-1qfd0","type":"parent-child","created_at":"2026-04-01T19:16:49.080966790Z","created_by":"ubuntu","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""}],"comments":[{"id":2908,"issue_id":"asupersync-1qfd0.513","author":"BeigeCardinal","text":"Implemented the service-buffer liveness fix in src/service/buffer.rs. Root cause: BufferFuture::Active woke ready_wakers on normal completion but did not wake sibling inner_wakers, even though the drop path already did; with multiple waiters behind a single-flight inner service, only the last service-level readiness waker fired and earlier buffered requests could stay stranded. Fix: drain inner_wakers alongside ready_wakers on Active->Ready, and add a focused regression using a single-flight test service with two sibling readiness waiters. Validation: rch exec -- env CARGO_TARGET_DIR=/tmp/rch-target-beigecardinal-buffer-test cargo test -j1 -p asupersync --lib active_completion_wakes_all_inner_readiness_waiters -- --nocapture => exit 0; rch exec -- env CARGO_TARGET_DIR=/tmp/rch-target-beigecardinal-buffer-check cargo check -p asupersync --lib => exit 0; rch exec -- env CARGO_TARGET_DIR=/tmp/rch-target-beigecardinal-buffer-clippy cargo clippy -j1 -p asupersync --lib -- -D warnings => exit 0; rustfmt --check src/service/buffer.rs => exit 0. Broad cargo fmt --check remains dirty outside this slice because tests/fabric_lab_integration.rs already had unrelated formatting drift in the shared worktree.","created_at":"2026-04-01T19:35:05Z"}]}
