+{"id":"asupersync-1qfd0.515","title":"[audit][distributed] RegionBridge snapshots must preserve caller-supplied time","description":"Fresh-eyes child under asupersync-1qfd0. RegionBridge::create_snapshot currently hardcodes Time::ZERO, so sync/replication snapshots lose chronology and sync_state.last_sync_time never reflects a truthful snapshot instant. Thread explicit Time through RegionBridge snapshot/sync paths and federation replication export call sites, preserve bounded scope, add focused regressions for snapshot timestamp propagation and sync_state timestamp tracking, and validate with rch-backed targeted tests/check/clippy plus fmt check.","status":"in_progress","priority":2,"issue_type":"bug","assignee":"Codex","created_at":"2026-04-01T20:31:41.632313835Z","created_by":"ubuntu","updated_at":"2026-04-01T20:52:58.021013775Z","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0,"labels":["audit","distributed","snapshot"],"dependencies":[{"issue_id":"asupersync-1qfd0.515","depends_on_id":"asupersync-1qfd0","type":"parent-child","created_at":"2026-04-01T20:31:41.632313835Z","created_by":"ubuntu","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""}],"comments":[{"id":2918,"issue_id":"asupersync-1qfd0.515","author":"Codex","text":"Implemented bounded snapshot-time propagation: RegionBridge sync/create_snapshot/upgrade_to_distributed now take explicit Time, sync/apply_snapshot persist last_sync_time, FederationBridge export_replication_transfer now takes explicit Time, and distributed/fabric/e2e callsites were updated with focused timestamp regressions. Validation so far: rch exec cargo check --lib --features messaging-fabric passed on vmi1293453; exact rch regression test retries are still running; broader all-targets/clippy runs are currently noisy because of unrelated workspace/toolchain and remote-worker issues.","created_at":"2026-04-01T20:52:58Z"}]}
 {"id":"asupersync-1qfd0.516","title":"[audit] Fresh-eyes audit of unaudited RNG/random surface","description":"Bounded support slice under the fresh-eyes audit epic. Select one currently unaudited random/RNG-related source file, audit it carefully for correctness and determinism issues, update audit_index.jsonl with the verdict, and only widen to code changes if a concrete bug is found and fixed with targeted rch validation.","status":"closed","priority":1,"issue_type":"task","estimated_minutes":90,"created_at":"2026-04-01T20:41:43.090237616Z","created_by":"DarkCastle","updated_at":"2026-04-01T20:44:27.733135385Z","closed_at":"2026-04-01T20:44:27.732699856Z","close_reason":"Diff audit completed; no bugs found","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0,"labels":["audit","exploration","random"],"dependencies":[{"issue_id":"asupersync-1qfd0.516","depends_on_id":"asupersync-1qfd0","type":"parent-child","created_at":"2026-04-01T20:41:43.090237616Z","created_by":"DarkCastle","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""}],"comments":[{"id":2912,"issue_id":"asupersync-1qfd0.516","author":"DarkCastle","text":"Starting bounded fresh-eyes audit slice under asupersync-1qfd0. Initial filename-only scan showed the obvious RNG files (src/util/entropy.rs and src/util/det_rng.rs) are already covered in audit_index.jsonl, so I am broadening to symbol-level discovery to pick a genuinely unaudited random-adjacent source file before touching code or the audit index.","created_at":"2026-04-01T20:42:04Z"},{"id":2914,"issue_id":"asupersync-1qfd0.516","author":"DarkCastle","text":"Pivoting this child from filename-based RNG hunting to a diff audit on src/decoding.rs. Rationale: the obvious entropy files are already fully covered, but src/decoding.rs still owns block-seed derivation and has post-audit changes on 2026-04-01 after its last deep audit entry dated 2026-03-29. I am reviewing only the post-audit delta and will either record a clean diff-audit in audit_index.jsonl or fix a concrete regression if one surfaces.","created_at":"2026-04-01T20:43:49Z"},{"id":2915,"issue_id":"asupersync-1qfd0.516","author":"DarkCastle","text":"Diff audit result on src/decoding.rs: SOUND. The entire post-2026-03-29 delta is a non-semantic  binding added after renaming  ->  so non-tracing builds still satisfy unused-variable linting while tracing builds retain structured error emission. No change to block-seed derivation, decoder construction, reject mapping, or failure state transitions.","created_at":"2026-04-01T20:44:02Z"},{"id":2916,"issue_id":"asupersync-1qfd0.516","author":"DarkCastle","text":"Clarification for the prior note: the reviewed delta in src/decoding.rs is exactly the cfg(not(feature = \"tracing-integration\")) unused-variable binding that keeps non-tracing builds lint-clean after renaming Err(_err) to Err(err). This is semantically inert and does not alter decoding behavior.","created_at":"2026-04-01T20:44:27Z"}]}
 {"id":"asupersync-1qfd0.52","title":"[audit][websocket] Remove ambient entropy from client frame masking","description":"src/net/websocket/frame.rs currently generates client masking keys with direct getrandom::fill(), and src/audit/ambient.rs treats that as a critical unresolved ambient-authority violation. Replace the frame-mask path with EntropySource plumbing, use Cx entropy where WebSocket client/server/split APIs already have a context, add targeted regressions, and update the ambient-audit catalog/tests so the critical finding is actually retired.","status":"tombstone","priority":1,"issue_type":"bug","assignee":"SilverQuarry","estimated_minutes":60,"created_at":"2026-03-09T18:54:49.707067660Z","created_by":"ubuntu","updated_at":"2026-03-23T07:08:35.747405470Z","closed_at":"2026-03-23T07:08:35.747405470Z","close_reason":"Completed: websocket masking entropy now flows through EntropySource/Cx; rch cargo check --all-targets and focused websocket/audit lib tests passed; repo-wide clippy frontier is unrelated in http_client/debounce","source_repo":".","deleted_at":"2026-03-23T07:08:35.747380313Z","deleted_by":"system","delete_reason":"merge deletion","original_type":"bug","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0,"labels":["audit","determinism","security","websocket"],"dependencies":[{"issue_id":"asupersync-1qfd0.52","depends_on_id":"asupersync-1qfd0","type":"parent-child","created_at":"2026-03-09T18:54:49.707067660Z","created_by":"ubuntu","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""}]}
 {"id":"asupersync-1qfd0.52.1","title":"[audit][websocket] Repair encode_with_entropy borrow call sites after entropy plumbing","description":"The in-progress ambient-entropy websocket changes updated FrameCodec::encode_with_entropy to take &Frame, but several call sites in src/net/websocket/frame.rs, src/net/websocket/client.rs, and src/net/websocket/split.rs still pass Frame by value. That leaves the repo uncompilable and blocks rch-backed validation for unrelated work. Apply the minimal borrow-site fixes only, preserve the existing entropy-plumbing changes, add no new behavior beyond restoring compilation, and validate with rch-backed targeted cargo commands.","status":"tombstone","priority":1,"issue_type":"bug","assignee":"CoralCompass","created_at":"2026-03-09T19:10:35.862874674Z","created_by":"AmberHarbor","updated_at":"2026-03-23T07:08:29.966871456Z","closed_at":"2026-03-23T07:08:29.966871456Z","close_reason":"Current tree already satisfies bead contract; websocket encode_with_entropy call sites already borrow frames","source_repo":".","deleted_at":"2026-03-23T07:08:29.966849596Z","deleted_by":"system","delete_reason":"merge deletion","original_type":"bug","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0,"dependencies":[{"issue_id":"asupersync-1qfd0.52.1","depends_on_id":"asupersync-1qfd0.52","type":"parent-child","created_at":"2026-03-09T19:10:35.862874674Z","created_by":"AmberHarbor","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""}],"comments":[{"id":2476,"issue_id":"asupersync-1qfd0.52.1","author":"CoralCompass","text":"Audit result: current tree already satisfies this bead.\n\nSource evidence:\n- `src/net/websocket/frame.rs:393` still defines `FrameCodec::encode_with_entropy(&self, frame: &Frame, ...)`.\n- `src/net/websocket/frame.rs:774` already borrows in the encoder implementation (`self.encode_with_entropy(&frame, ...)`).\n- Client-side websocket call paths already borrow frames at `src/net/websocket/client.rs:438`, `:463`, `:485`, `:591`, and `:597`; the helper that reaches the codec also takes `frame: &Frame` at `src/net/websocket/client.rs:603`.\n- Split-side websocket call paths already borrow frames at `src/net/websocket/split.rs:292`, `:437`, `:548`, and `:577`; the helpers that reach the codec take `frame: &Frame` at `src/net/websocket/split.rs:444` and `:584`.\n- File-local formatting check passed: `rustfmt --edition 2024 --check src/net/websocket/frame.rs src/net/websocket/client.rs src/net/websocket/split.rs`.\n\nConclusion: the borrow-site repair described by this bead is already present in the current tree; no code change required.","created_at":"2026-03-10T05:45:41Z"}]}
