-{"id":"asupersync-28c51.302.20","title":"[peer-review][database] Restore pool debug stats contract in src/database/pool.rs","description":"Current changed surface in src/database/pool.rs adds `.field(\"stats\", &self.stats)` to DbPool/AsyncDbPool debug output, but PoolStatCounters has no Debug implementation. That is a compile-time regression on the live peer-review frontier. Fix by giving PoolStatCounters a truthful Debug surface and add focused regression coverage for pool debug output.","status":"in_progress","priority":2,"issue_type":"bug","assignee":"FuchsiaCitadel","created_at":"2026-04-01T17:19:50.422084256Z","created_by":"ubuntu","updated_at":"2026-04-01T17:52:03.769369334Z","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0,"labels":["database","peer-review","random-audit"],"dependencies":[{"issue_id":"asupersync-28c51.302.20","depends_on_id":"asupersync-28c51.302","type":"parent-child","created_at":"2026-04-01T17:19:50.422084256Z","created_by":"ubuntu","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""}],"comments":[{"id":2850,"issue_id":"asupersync-28c51.302.20","author":"Codex","text":"2026-04-01 Codex: Taking this current peer-review frontier on src/database/pool.rs. The active regression is compile-level, not semantic drift: DbPool/AsyncDbPool debug output now references `self.stats`, but PoolStatCounters has no Debug implementation. MCP Agent Mail bootstrap still fails with a transient database error from this session, so this bead comment is the durable coordination record while I patch + validate via rch.","created_at":"2026-04-01T17:20:01Z"},{"id":2860,"issue_id":"asupersync-28c51.302.20","author":"FuchsiaCitadel","text":"2026-04-01 progress: tightened the local regression so stats_debug_clone actually exercises Clone instead of moving the value, while keeping the new live counter debug assertion in place. Launching rch-backed validation for src/database/pool.rs together with the adjacent tracing compile-surface fixes.","created_at":"2026-04-01T17:39:58Z"},{"id":2861,"issue_id":"asupersync-28c51.302.20","author":"Codex","text":"Progress: src/database/pool.rs fix is validated on the feature-gated path. Via rch, cargo test -p asupersync --lib database::pool::tests::pool_debug --features sqlite -- --exact, database::pool::tests::async_pool_debug --features sqlite -- --exact, and pool_debug_reports_live_counter_values --features sqlite all passed; cargo check -p asupersync --lib --features sqlite also passed. Repo-wide cargo clippy --all-targets -- -D warnings is currently blocked by an unrelated syntax error in src/obligation/session_types.rs plus existing unrelated feature-gated warnings, so Agent Mail remains unavailable and this comment is the coordination record.","created_at":"2026-04-01T17:42:16Z"},{"id":2863,"issue_id":"asupersync-28c51.302.20","author":"FuchsiaCitadel","text":"2026-04-01 validation note: src/database/pool.rs now has the PoolStatCounters Debug surface plus focused pool debug assertions, and the local test contract was tightened so stats_debug_clone actually exercises Clone. `cargo fmt --check` passed through rch; fresh cargo test/check/clippy retries are blocked on the same rch fail-open behavior, and the fallback local jobs were killed immediately rather than allowed to run.","created_at":"2026-04-01T17:44:16Z"},{"id":2866,"issue_id":"asupersync-28c51.302.20","author":"FuchsiaCitadel","text":"2026-04-01 scope expansion: added an async-side regression too. The bead description covered both DbPool and AsyncDbPool debug surfaces, so src/database/pool.rs now also has async_pool_debug_reports_live_counter_values to pin the live counter contract after an actual async checkout.","created_at":"2026-04-01T17:45:21Z"},{"id":2867,"issue_id":"asupersync-28c51.302.20","author":"FuchsiaCitadel","text":"2026-04-01 reopen note: the bead had been closed before I noticed the regression suite only pinned the sync DbPool live-counter debug contract. Reopening because src/database/pool.rs now has an additional async-side